C\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Meanwhile, remove log from mould (see tip) and place on wire rack.  Allow to stand for 5 minutes before coating log evenly with icing. Return to freezer until ready to serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Chocolate Icing","content":["85 g water, plus extra for soaking","110 g caster sugar","65 g double cream","2 gelatine leaves","40 g cocoa powder, unsweetened"]},{"title":"Tangerine Sorbet","content":["450 g tangerines or clementines, peeled, quartered then frozen","70 g icing sugar","1 Tbsp Cointreau"]},{"title":"Chocolate Ice Cream","content":["3 large eggs, separated","100 g caster sugar","250 g mascarpone","2 tsp cocoa powder"]}],"id":"r102861","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-soqKCex34fs\/XZWc3YhZHyI\/AAAAAAAAef0\/KW3p9zgB1EUopNuHnF73BmCjBejsvxnugCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_8-merQB49IgUKmsl.png","title":"Tangerine and Chocolate Log (French)","publishedAt":"2016-12-05T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"9.3 g","fat":"26.5 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"42.5 g","calories":"1891 kJ \/ 450 kcal"},"usefulItems":"piping bag, straight sided loaf tin, wire rack, baking paper, refrigerator, freezer","hintsAndTricks":["The chocolate icing can be prepared the day before.","Prepare the ice log a day ahead.","When drawing the 'gutter', if the chocolate is too soft, freeze it for 30 minutes - 1 hour until firm enough to draw and hold the gutter shape.","To remove log from the mould, dip base in hot water for a few seconds to loosen before turning out.","To slice log, dip a long sharp knife in hot water then wipe dry before cutting slices."],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","8h 55m","6 portions"]}